defaultLocal government spends £58 billion
default per year procuring goods and services. This note sets out how DCLG is 
defaultincentivising
default local government to open up its procurement practices, and become more efficient, transparent and accountable to local communities.
default&#xa0;
defaultSignificant changes have been made to central government procurement, examined recently by the Public Administration Select Committee in their report published on 16 July 2013
default. The principles behind those changes are the ones councils should be adopting, such as eliminating Pre Qualification Questionnaires for low value contracts as discussed on page 6. 
