default, t
defaulthe Federation for Small Businesses 
defaultpublished research which found 
defaultthat
default councils are transforming their procurement process. Specifically they found that there has been a noticed increase in the number of local authorities who adopt different processes for below EU threshold tenders (85% from 74% in 2012)
default&#xa0;
defaultW
defaulte 
defaultrecognise
default progress has been made
default, 
defaulthowever 
defaultthere are still too many councils using overly bureaucratic, disproportionate procurement processes, which unnecessarily discriminate against smaller businesses, and which are not transparent to 
defaultt
defaultheir local communities. 
defaultThis has been highlighted by the Mystery Shopper Scheme, which is discussed on page 7. 
