defaultGoverning legislation and recommended practice 
default&#xa0;
defaultCentral government clearly has a role to play in ensuring legislation promotes the procurement principles we advocate, whilst allowing significant freedom and flexibility to allow local practices to be adapted to suit local markets and contracts.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe will shortly be undertaking a significant consultation on procurement reforms across the whole public sector, which follow on from Lord Young’s report 
defaultGrowing Your 
defaultBusiness
default. The consultation will focus on some key themes: 
